---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Booking Terms & Conditions"
	description="Booking terms and conditions for Balance Performance Physiotherapy."
>
	<PageHero
		title="&amp; Conditions"
		highlight="Terms"
		breadcrumb="Terms &amp; Conditions"
	/>
	<section class="rich-content">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Booking Terms and Conditions</h2>
			<p>To secure your initial appointment with one of our clinicians, we require card details/payment in full from all patients, including those with insurance coverage.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Self paying patients</strong> &mdash; we require payment in full and card details will be requested over the phone ahead of your appointment to confirm your booking.</li>
				<li>No payment will be taken without your consent, unless we are unable to contact you within 7 days of an outstanding payment.</li>
				<li>Please be reassured that all card details are stored securely, are not accessible and in accordance with GDPR Regulations.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Insurance Patients</h2>
			<p>Balance Physiotherapy is registered with and bill directly Bupa and Axa PPP, Bupa Global &amp; AXA Global.</p>
			<p>We are also recognised by WPA, Helix, Exeter, Vitality and Aviva but we do not bill them directly.</p>
			<p>We ask all our clients to check their individual insurance policies regarding payment and direct claims prior to their initial visit.</p>
			<p>It is your responsibility as the client/patient to be aware of your sessions used and to not go over your allowance. You will be liable to pay for any sessions not covered under your allocation from your healthcare insurance provider.</p>
			<p>If you are insured, please ensure you:</p>
			<ol>
				<li>Obtain a valid authorisation number before your scheduled appointment.</li>
				<li>Provide your authorisation number and policy number prior to booking.</li>
				<li>Save your credit or debit card ahead of your first appointment. We will only use this to collect an excess if your insurer asks us to do so.</li>
			</ol>
			<p>Without this information, you will be asked to pay for your treatment upfront, and you can then reclaim the cost directly from your insurer using the invoice and receipt we provide.</p>

			<h2>Appointment Confirmation</h2>
			<p>Please note that Initial Appointments will only be confirmed once payment has been made at least 48 hours in advance.</p>
			<p>Balance Performance Physiotherapy has a cancellation (or change of appointment) policy of 24 hours (48 hours for Vojta Therapy). Failure to give this notification or failing to attend an appointment will incur the full cost of the intended appointment. An answer machine facility is available every day or alternatively e-mail us 24/48 hours in advance at <a href="mailto:admin@balancephysio.com">admin@balancephysio.com</a>.</p>
			<p>If you'd like to view our privacy policy please see <a href="/privacy-policy">our website</a>. Please sign to agree these terms &amp; conditions and consent to treatment given.</p>
			<p>As part of our debt reduction policy Balance Performance Physiotherapy Ltd stores patient's credit card details on file. Relevant card details will be requested from you by our front of house team, but will only be used in the instance of outstanding debt exceeding 1 month. You can use your stored CC for payment of your treatment or insurance excess if you wish to. Our practice management software Mindbody meets the credit card industry's highest security standards. Each year, Mindbody satisfies a rigorous audit to ensure the highest standard encrypting your credit card numbers and only partial credit card information is visible in our software. To review the privacy policy of Mindbody or read their PCI compliance information please see our website for this information.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
